UA Families: Tomorrow, Tuesday, Sept. 8, is the first day of virtual school! Students in grades 6-12 begin online at 7:30 a.m. Students in grades 2-5 start at 8 a.m., and kindergarten and first grade students begin at 8:30 a.m. Visit the "Virtual Learning Resources" page on our website for more details.

We can't wait to see you tomorrow morning, Gryphons! Let the 2020-21 school year begin!!

Way to go, graduates! It's a great day to be a Gryphon!

post_text:
Attention Summer School Families:

You can drop off medications and immunizations for your student on the first day of summer school between 7:10 a.m. and 8 a.m. at the front of the building. There will be a table outside with nursing staff present to make sure all paperwork is filled out and to answer any questions you may have.

All medication must be dropped off by a parent/legal guardian. Permission slips for the medication will need to be filled out at that time.

If you need to drop medication off at a different time, please contact the nursing office (hidalgos@universityacademy.org or leavittb@universityacademy.org) to set up an appointment.

Thank you!

Big things keep happening for our 2020 graduates! MyAun Boyd was surprised yesterday by The Kansas City Chiefs, who awarded her the Len Dawson Scholarship and a new laptop. The Len Dawson Scholarship has been helping local students go to college for nearly 50 years.

In addition, Paulina Garcia and Jayden Johnson have been awarded Student Alumni Success Scholarships, worth $20,000 over four years, thanks to generous donors through Friends of University Academy.

Big time congratulations, Gryphons!!

COMPUTER RETURNS

If you checked out a UA computer for the end of the school year, we are holding a drop-off event this Wednesday, June 24, and Thursday, June 25, from 9 a.m. - noon in the UA parking lot. Our IT department, Mr. Klug and Mr. Eklund, will be on hand to receive the computers. You won't even have to get out of the car!

If you cannot make either of those times, please email helpdesk@universityacademy.org, and we'll work with you to find an alternative time. Thanks!

Free COVID-19 testing will be available to all area residents on June 25 thanks to our preschool partner, United Inner City Services - UICS, and several community partners including Heart to Heart International, DeLaSalle Education Center, University of Kansas Medical Center and St. James Catholic Church.

Visit DeLaSalle Education Center (3737 Troost Avenue) on Thursday, June 25 from 9 a.m. - 6 p.m. Pre-registrations are best, but walk-ups are acceptable as well.

post_text:
UA Upper School Again Honored by U.S. News Top High Schools Rankings

UA Upper School has been named one of the top high schools in the U.S. every year since 2012. This year, UA Upper was ranked the #1 charter high school in Missouri, the #20 public high school in Missouri, and one of the top high schools in the KC bi-state metro area. The rankings factor in AP course participation, AP tests passed, state testing performance, and graduation rates. We focus more on dual credit than AP, but we have increased our AP offerings over the past few years. Great job students, staff and administrators!

Did you know!? The Wellness Center continues to be a resource to students and families. In order to align with current clinical social distancing procedures, policies are as follows:

1. Call 816-412-5978 or email cmh@universityacademy.org to schedule an appointment.
2. Nearly ALL appointments will be by portal/email, telephone or video chat. Download Zoom on your computer, tablet or telephone for a video chat appointment.
3. Only in rare situations will in-person appointments be available.

Click on the link below for helpful information about COVID-19. If your questions are not answered there, you can call the Children's Mercy hotline number, (816) 302-8800, which provides options for questions from parents regarding their child's health.

STATE CHAMPS!!! Our Upper School's academic decathlon team has been named the Missouri State Champion and qualified for nationals! This is the team's ninth time qualifying for nationals in the past 10 years. They will travel to Anchorage, Alaska, for the competition in April.

Team members include: Tessa Blythe, MyAun Boyd, David McDonald, Paulina Garcia, Elijah Hudson-Moore, Damion Tripp, Jaydah Burton and Jaden Lee. They are led by Mr. Burdette. CONGRATULATIONS to all!

Brian Smith, a member of UA's Class of 2012, was inducted into the Gryphons' Athletic Hall of Fame this week.

Brian earned All-State football honors while at UA and was also an Academic All-American. He then played football for the University of Central Missouri, where he also earned his bachelor's degree. Brian is now on the coaching staff at UCM. Congratulations to this outstanding representative of University Academy!

Chamber of Commerce Touchdown Celebration

Show Us Your #TouchdownKansasCity!

We know how The Kansas City Chiefs celebrate when they score. The Greater Kansas City Chamber of Commerce wants to see how YOU celebrate!

Take a video of your family, your friends, your coworkers, your kids, your pets or even yourself scoring a touchdown and how you celebrate. Whether it’s a special touchdown dance, a high-five, a backflip, or anything else, post it to social media beginning TODAY, Monday, Jan. 27, and show us your #touchdownkansascity.

Tag the Chamber on Twitter and Instagram at @kcchamber and use the hashtags #touchdownkansascity and #kcchamber. Tag the Greater Kansas City Chamber of Commerce on Facebook with the same hashtags.

Let’s get this trending! We want the WORLD to see how much Chiefs Kingdom loves our Chiefs no matter what part of the country we’re in!

Name of social campaign: Show Us Your #TouchdownKansasCity.

Hashtags: #Touchdownkansascity #kcchamber

Tag @kcchamber on Twitter and Instagram.

REMINDER: The UA Wellness Center still has flu shots available. Nobody wants the flu! Don’t let a high fever, runny nose, body aches and sore throat keep your children out of school and the activities they love. Have your student get a flu shot at the Wellness Center, and stay protected all season long. Flu shots are free for students!

Please contact the Wellness Center at 816-412-5978 or stop by to pick up paperwork .

post_text:
Just call them the Comeback Kings... The UA's boys' basketball team erased a 27-point first half deficit to defeat Grandview Christian 64-61 in the championship game of Summit Christian's Eagle Invitational last night!

Juniors Steven Strong and Quran Taylor earned spots the all-tournament team, and Strong was also named tournament MVP. Congrats to our Gryphon players and coaches on an incredible week of games at Hy-Vee Arena!

The girls' basketball team also played hard this week, coming up just short in the seventh place game against Hogan last night, 26-33.

post_text: Our annual Harvester's food drive was a success! Upper School students distributed empty grocery bags throughout the neighborhood a couple weeks ago, and last Saturday students went back around and collected approximately 250 bags filled with donated food items. The bags were taken to the food banks at St. Therese Little Flower and St. Francis Xavier. We love serving our community!
